  "identifier": "HB 671",
  "title": "AN ACT relating to the protection of elected officials.",
  "abstract": "Create a new section of KRS Chapter 16 to define \"statewide-elected official\"; require the Department of Kentucky State Police to investigate a credible threat to kill or seriously injure a statewide-elected official; require the department to make an assessment of the threat after conducting an investigation; require the department, after making a determination that a threat is a viable threat, to identify ways to mitigate or eliminate the threat.",
